obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (8913)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes `1. 22nd April 1969, vide Notification No. S.O.1525, dated 21st April, 1969, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00016_196653_1517807324379&sectionId=8913&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00016_196653_1517807324379
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Jawaharlal Nehru University`
  line `Act, 1966.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall come into force on such date^1as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (8914)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00016_196653_1517807324379&sectionId=8914&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00016_196653_1517807324379
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "College" means a college maintained by the University;`
  line
  line `(b) "Hall" means a unit of residence, by whatever name called, for students of the University`
  line `provided, maintained or recognised by it;`
  line
  line `(c) "recognised institution" means an institution of higher learning maintained or recognised by,`
  line `or associated with, the University;`
  line
  line `(d) "prescribed" means prescribed by Statutes, Ordinances or Regulations;`
  line
  line `(e) "Statutes", "Ordinances" and "Regulations" mean, respectively, the Statutes, Ordinances and`
  line `Regulations of the University made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(f) "University" means the Jawaharlal Nehru University.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (8915)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `The University.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00016_196653_1517807324379&sectionId=8915&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00016_196653_1517807324379
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be constituted in the Union territory of Delhi a University by the`
  line `name of "Jawaharlal Nehru University".`
  line
  line `(2) The first Chancellor and the first Vice-Chancellor of the University and the first members of the`
  line `Court, the Executive Council and the Academic Council and all persons who may hereafter become such`
  line `officers or members so long as they continue to hold such office or membership are hereby constituted a`
  line `body corporate by the name of "Jawaharlal Nehru University".`
  line
  line `(3) The University shall have perpetual succession and a common seal, and shall sue and be sued by`
  line `the said name.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (8916)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title Objects.
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00016_196653_1517807324379&sectionId=8916&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00016_196653_1517807324379
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `The objects of the University shall be to disseminate and advance knowledge, wisdom`
  line `and understanding by teaching and research and by the example and influence of its corporate life and in`
  line `particular the objects set out in the First Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (8917)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Powers of the University.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00016_196653_1517807324379&sectionId=8917&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00016_196653_1517807324379
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `The University shall have the following powers, namely:--`
  line
  line `(1) to provide for instruction including the method of correspondence courses in such branches of`
  line `learning as the University may from time to time determine, and to make provision for research and`
  line `for the advancement and dissemination of knowledge;`
  line
  line `(2) to establish within the Union territory of Delhi or outside that territory such Special Centres`
  line `and Specialised Laboratories and such other units for research and instruction as are necessary for the`
  line `furtherance of its objects;`
  line
  line `(3) to organise and to undertake extra-mural teaching and extension services;`
  line
  line `(4) to hold examinations and grant diplomas or certificates to, and confer degrees and other`
  line `academic distinctions on, persons and to withdraw any such diplomas, certificates, degrees or other`
  line `academic distinctions for good and sufficient cause;`
  line
  line `(5) to confer honorary degrees or other academic distinctions in the manner laid down in the`
  line Statutes;
  line
  line `(6) to create such teaching, administrative and other posts as the University may deem necessary,`
  line `from time to time, and to make appointments thereto;`
  line
  line `(7) to appoint or recognise persons as Professors, Readers or Lecturers or otherwise as teachers of`
  line `the University;`
  line
  line `(8) to institute and award Fellowships, Scholarships, Exhibitions and prizes;`
  line
  line `(9) to establish and maintain Colleges and Halls, to recognise, guide, supervise and control Halls`
  line `not maintained by the University and other accommodation for students, and to withdraw any such`
  line recognition;
  line
  line `(10) to regulate and enforce discipline among students and employees of the University and to`
  line `take such disciplinary measures in this regard as may be deemed necessary;`
  line
  line `(11) to make arrangements for promoting health and general welfare of students and employees`
  line `of the University;`
  line
  line `(12) to determine and provide for examinations for admission into the University;`
  line
  line `(13) to recognise for any purpose, either in whole or in part, any institution or members or`
  line `students thereof on such terms and conditions as may, from time to time, be prescribed and to`
  line `withdraw such recognition;`
  line
  line `(14) to co-operate with any other University, authority or association or any other public or`
  line `private body having in view the promotion of purposes and objects similar to those of the University`
  line `for such purposes as may be agreed upon, on such terms and conditions as may, from time to time, be`
  line prescribed;
  line
  line `(15) to enter into any agreement for the incorporation in the University of any other institution`
  line `and for taking over its rights, properties and liabilities and for any other purpose not repugnant to this`
  line Act;
  line
  line `(16) to demand and receive payment of such fees and other charges as may be prescribed, from`
  line `time to time;`
  line
  line `(17) to receive donations and to acquire, hold, manage and dispose of any property movable or`
  line `immovable, including trust or endowed property within or outside the Union territory of Delhi, for the`
  line `purposes or objects of the University, and to invest funds in such manner as the University thinks fit;`
  line
  line `(18) to make provision for research and advisory services; and for that purpose to enter into such`
  line `arrangements with other institutions or bodies as the University may deem necessary;`
  line
  line `(19) to provide for the printing, reproduction and publication of research and other work which`
  line `may be issued by the University;`
  line
  line `(20) to borrow, with the approval of the Central Government, on the security of the University`
  line `property, money for the purposes of the University;`
  line
  line `(21) to do all such things as may be necessary, incidental or conducive to the attainment of all or`
  line `any of the objects of the University.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (8918)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Jurisdiction of the University.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00016_196653_1517807324379&sectionId=8918&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00016_196653_1517807324379
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The jurisdiction of the University shall extend to all Colleges`
  line `and recognised institutions.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in clause (13) of section 5, the Jawaharlal Nehru University`
  line `shall not grant recognition, either in whole or in part, to any institution which has already been recognised`
  line `by the University of Delhi unless the Central Government, after consultation with the University of Delhi,`
  line `authorises the Jawaharlal Nehru University to do so.`
  line
  line `(3) On and from the date of the recognition either in whole or in part of an institution by the`
  line `Jawaharlal Nehru University under sub- section (2), the University of Delhi shall to the extent of such`
  line `recognition cease to have jurisdiction over that institution.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (8919)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Powers and jurisdiction in respect of institution or body outside the Union territory of Delhi.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00016_196653_1517807324379&sectionId=8919&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00016_196653_1517807324379
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in section 5,--`
  line
  line `(a) where any institution or body established outside the Union territory of Delhi seeks`
  line `recognition from the University, or`
  line
  line `(b) where the University establishes and maintains any institution or body outside the Union`
  line `territory of Delhi,`
  line
  line `then the powers and jurisdiction of the University shall extend to such institution or body subject to--`
  line
  line `(i) the laws in force in the State within which, and`
  line
  line `(ii) the rules and regulations of the University within whose jurisdiction,`
  line
  line `the said institution or body is situated.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (8920)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title Visitor.
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00016_196653_1517807324379&sectionId=8920&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00016_196653_1517807324379
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The President of India shall be the Visitor of the University.`
  line
  line `(2) The Visitor may, from time to time, appoint one or more persons to review the work and progress`
  line `of the University and to submit a report thereon; and upon receipt of that report, the Visitor may, after`
  line `obtaining the views of the Executive Council thereon, take such action and issue such directions as he`
  line `considers necessary in respect of any of the matters dealt with in the report and the University shall be`
  line `bound to comply with such directions.`
  line
  line `(3) The Visitor shall also have the right to cause an inspection to be made by such person or persons`
  line `as he may direct of the University, its buildings, laboratories and equipment and of any institution`
  line `maintained by the University, and also of the examinations, teaching and other work conducted or done`
  line `by the University and to cause an inquiry to be made in respect of any matter connected with the`
  line University.
  line
  line `(4) The Visitor shall in every case give notice to the University of his intention to cause an inspection`
  line `or inquiry to be made, and the University shall be entitled to appoint a representative who shall have the`
  line `right to be present and be heard at such inspection or inquiry.`
  line
  line `(5) The Visitor may address the Vice-Chancellor with reference to the result of such inspection and`
  line `inquiry, and the Vice-Chancellor shall communicate to the Executive Council the views of the Visitor`
  line `with such advice as the Visitor may offer upon the action to be taken thereon.`
  line
  line `(6) The Executive Council shall communicate through the Vice-Chancellor to the Visitor such action,`
  line `if any, as it is proposed to take or has been taken upon the result of such inspection or inquiry.`
  line
  line `(7) Where the Executive Council does not, within a reasonable time, take action to the satisfaction of`
  line `the Visitor, the Visitor may, after considering any explanation furnished or representation made by the`
  line `Executive Council, issue such directions as he may think fit and the Executive Council shall be bound to`
  line `comply with such directions.`
  line
  line `(8) The Visitor may by order in writing annul any proceeding of the University which is not in`
  line `conformity with this Act, the Statutes or the Ordinances.`
  line
  line `(9) The Visitor shall also have such other powers as may be prescribed by the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (8921)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Officers of the University.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00016_196653_1517807324379&sectionId=8921&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00016_196653_1517807324379
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be a Chancellor appointed in the manner prescribed`
  line `by the Statutes who shall be the Head of the University.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chancellor shall, if present, preside at convocation of the University for conferring degrees`
  line `and all meetings of the Court.`
  line
  line `(3) There shall be a Vice-Chancellor appointed in the manner prescribed by the Statutes who shall be`
  line `the principal executive and Academic Officer of the University and ex officio Chairman of the Executive`
  line `Council, Academic Council and Finance Committee and he shall, in the absence of the Chancellor preside`
  line `at any convocation for conferring degrees and also at any meeting of the Court.`
  line
  line `(4) There shall be one or more Rectors who shall be appointed in such manner and with such powers`
  line `and duties as may be prescribed by the Statutes.`
  line
  line `(5) There shall be a Dean for each School of Study who shall be appointed in such manner and with`
  line `such powers and duties as may be prescribed by the Statutes.`
  line
  line `(6) There shall be a Registrar who shall act as Secretary of the Court, the Executive Council and the`
  line `Academic Council and he shall be appointed in such manner and with such powers and duties as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Statutes.`
  line
  line `(7) There shall be a Finance Officer who shall be the Secretary of the Finance Committee and`
  line `exercise such powers and perform such duties as may be prescribed by the Statutes.`
  line
  line `(8) There shall be such other officers as provided for in the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (8922)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Authorities of the University.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00016_196653_1517807324379&sectionId=8922&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00016_196653_1517807324379
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `The authorities of the University shall be the Court, the`
  line `Executive Council, the Academic Council, the Schools of Studies, the Finance Committee and such other`
  line `authorities as may be declared by the Statutes to be authorities of the University.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (8923)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `The Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00016_196653_1517807324379&sectionId=8923&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00016_196653_1517807324379
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Court shall be the supreme authority of the University, and its constitution`
  line `and the terms of office of its members shall be prescribed by the Statutes.`
  line
  line `(2) The Court shall have the power to review the acts of the Executive Council and the Academic`
  line `Council (save when these authorities have acted in accordance with the powers conferred upon them`
  line `under this Act, the Statutes or the Ordinances) and shall exercise all the powers of the University not`
  line `otherwise provided for by this Act or the Statutes:`
  line
  line `Provided that the power of review under this sub-section shall not be exercised except by a majority`
  line `of the total membership of the Court and by a majority of not less than two-thirds of the members of the`
  line `Court present and voting.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (8924)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `The Executive Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00016_196653_1517807324379&sectionId=8924&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00016_196653_1517807324379
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Executive Council shall be the executive body of the`
  line `University, and its constitution and the terms of office of its members, other than ex officio members,`
  line `shall be prescribed by the Statutes.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall be in charge of the general management and administration (including the revenue and`
  line `property) of the University.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (8925)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `The Academic Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00016_196653_1517807324379&sectionId=8925&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00016_196653_1517807324379
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Academic Council shall be the academic body of the`
  line `University, and its constitution and the terms of office of its members, other than ex officio members,`
  line `shall be prescribed by the Statutes.`
  line
  line `(2) The Academic Council shall, subject to the provisions of this Act, the Statutes and the Ordinances,`
  line `have the control and general regulation, and be responsible for the maintenance, of standards of`
  line `instruction, education and examination within the University, and shall exercise such other powers and`
  line `perform such other duties as may be conferred or imposed upon it by the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (8926)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `The Academic Advisory Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00016_196653_1517807324379&sectionId=8926&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00016_196653_1517807324379
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be constituted an Academic Advisory`
  line `Committee of the University which shall advise generally on the planning and development of the`
  line `University and keep under review the standard of education and research in the University.--`
  line
  line `(2) The Committee shall consist of`
  line
  line `(a) not more than seven persons of high academic standing who shall be appointed in such`
  line `manner as may be prescribed by the statutes, and`
  line
  line `(b) the Vice-Chancellor.`
  line
  line `(3) The Visitor may determine a date with effect from which the Academic Advisory Committee shall`
  line `stand dissolved.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (8927)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title Statutes.
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00016_196653_1517807324379&sectionId=8927&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00016_196653_1517807324379
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Statutes may provide for all or any of the`
  line `following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the constitution, powers and duties of the authorities and other bodies of the University, the`
  line `qualifications and disqualifications for membership of such authorities and other bodies, appointment`
  line `and removal of members thereof and other matters connected therewith;`
  line
  line `(b) the appointment, powers and duties of the officers of the University;`
  line
  line `(c) the appointment, terms and conditions of service and the powers and duties of the employees`
  line `of the University;`
  line
  line `(d) the terms and conditions under which institutions may be associated with the University;`
  line
  line `(e) the administration of the University, the establishment and abolition of Colleges, institutions`
  line `and Halls, the grant and withdrawal of recognition to institutions, the institution of Fellowships,`
  line `Awards and the like, the conferment of degrees and other academic distinctions and the grant of`
  line `diplomas and certificates;`
  line
  line `(f) any other matter which is necessary for the proper and effective management and conduct of`
  line `the affairs of the University and which by this Act is to be or may be provided by the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (8928)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Statutes how made.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00016_196653_1517807324379&sectionId=8928&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00016_196653_1517807324379
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The first Statutes are those set out in the Second Schedule.`
  line
  line `(2) The Executive Council may, from time to time, make new or additional Statutes or may amend or`
  line `repeal the Statutes in the manner hereafter in this section provided:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Executive Council shall not make any Statute or any amendment of a Statute`
  line `affecting the status, powers or constitution of any existing authority of the University until such authority`
  line `has been given an opportunity of expressing an opinion on the proposal, and any opinion so expressed`
  line `shall be in writing and shall be considered by the Executive Council:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no Statute shall be made by the Executive Council affecting the discipline of`
  line `students, and standards of instruction, education and examination except after consultation with the`
  line `Academic Council.`
  line
  line `(3) Every new Statute or addition to the Statutes or any amendment or repeal of a Statute shall`
  line `require the approval of the Visitor who may assent thereto or withhold assent on remit to the Executive`
  line `Council for consideration.`
  line
  line `(4) A new Statute or a Statute amending or repealing an existing Statute shall have no validity unless`
  line `it has been assented to by the Visitor.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (8929)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title Ordinances.
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00016_196653_1517807324379&sectionId=8929&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00016_196653_1517807324379
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act and the Statutes, the Ordinances may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the admission of students, the courses of study and the fees therefor, the qualifications`
  line `pertaining to degrees, diplomas, certificates and other academic distinctions, the conditions for the`
  line `grant of Fellowships, Awards and the like;`
  line
  line `(b) the conduct of examinations, including the terms of office and appointment of examiners, and`
  line `the conditions of residence of students and their general discipline;`
  line
  line `(c) the management of colleges and institutions maintained by the University;`
  line
  line `(d) any other matter which by this Act or the Statutes is to be or may be provided by the`
  line Ordinances.
  line
  line `(2) The first Ordinances shall be made by the Vice-Chancellor with the previous approval of the`
  line `Central Government and the Ordinances so made may be amended, repealed or added to at any time by`
  line `the Executive Council in the manner prescribed by the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (8930)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title Regulations.
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00016_196653_1517807324379&sectionId=8930&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00016_196653_1517807324379
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] The authorities of the University may make Regulations consistent with this`
  line `Act, the Statutes and the Ordinances for the conduct of their own business and that of the committees`
  line `appointed by them and not provided for by this Act, the Statutes or the Ordinances in the manner`
  line `prescribed by the Statutes.`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(2) Every Statute, Ordinance or Regulation made under this Act shall be published in the Offical`
  line Gazette.
  line
  line `(3) Every Statute, Ordinance or Regulation made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after`
  line `it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which`
  line `may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the`
  line `session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the Statute, Ordinance or Regulation or both Houses agree that the Statute,`
  line `Ordinance or Regulation should not be made, the Statute, Ordinance or Regulation shall thereafter have`
  line `effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such`
  line `modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under`
  line `that Statute, Ordinance or Regulation.]`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 18 renumbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 4 of 2005, s. 2 and Schedule (w.e.f.11-1-2005).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 2 and the Schedule, ibid. (w.e.f.11-1-2005).`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (8931)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Annual Report.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 25 of 2008, s. 6 (w.e.f. 5-12-2008).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00016_196653_1517807324379&sectionId=8931&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00016_196653_1517807324379
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) The annual report of the University shall be prepared under the direction of`
  line `the Executive Council and shall be submitted to the Court on or before such date as may be prescribed by`
  line `the Statutes and shall be considered by the Court at its annual meeting.`
  line
  line `(2) The Court may communicate its comments thereon to the Executive Council.`
  line
  line `^1[(3) A copy of the annual report, as prepared under sub-section (1), shall also be submitted to the`
  line `Central Government, which shall, as soon as may be, cause the same to be laid before both Houses of`
  line Parliament.]
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (8932)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Audit of accounts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 5-12-2008).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00016_196653_1517807324379&sectionId=8932&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00016_196653_1517807324379
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) The accounts of the University shall, once at least in every year and at`
  line `intervals of not more than fifteen months, be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India, or`
  line `any person authorised by him in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) The accounts, when audited shall be published in the Gazette of India, and a copy of the accounts`
  line `together with the audit report shall be submitted by the Registrar to the Visitor and to the Court.`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(3) A copy of the accounts, together with the audit report, shall also be submitted to the Central`
  line `Government, which shall, as soon as may be, cause the same to be laid before both Houses of Parliament.]`
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (8933)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Disputes as to constitution of the University authorities and bodies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00016_196653_1517807324379&sectionId=8933&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00016_196653_1517807324379
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `If any question arises`
  line `whether any person has been duly elected or appointed as, or is entitled to be, a member of any authority`
  line `or other body of the University, the matter shall be referred to the Visitor whose decision thereon shall be`
  line final.
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (8934)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Constitution of committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00016_196653_1517807324379&sectionId=8934&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00016_196653_1517807324379
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `Where any authority of the University is given power by this Act`
  line `or the Statutes to appoint committees, such committees shall, save as otherwise provided, consist of`
  line `members of the authority concerned and of such other persons (if any) as the authority in each case may`
  line `think fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (8935)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Filling of casual vacancies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00016_196653_1517807324379&sectionId=8935&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00016_196653_1517807324379
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `All casual vacancies among the members (other than ex officio`
  line `members) of any authority or other body of the University shall be filled, as soon as conveniently may be,`
  line `by the person or body who appointed, elected or co-opted the member whose place has become vacant,`
  line `and the person appointed, elected or co-opted to a casual vacancy shall be a member of such authority or`
  line `body for the residue of the term for which the person whose place he fills would have been a member.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (8936)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Proceedings of the University authorities and bodies not invalidated by vacancies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00016_196653_1517807324379&sectionId=8936&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00016_196653_1517807324379
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `No act`
  line `or proceedings of any authority or other body of the University shall be invalidated merely by reason of`
  line `the existence of a vacancy or vacancies among its members.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (8937)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Removal of difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00016_196653_1517807324379&sectionId=8937&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00016_196653_1517807324379
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of this Act,`
  line `the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions not`
  line `inconsistent with the purposes of this Act, as appear to it to be necessary or expedient for removing the`
  line difficulty.
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (8938)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Transitional provisions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00016_196653_1517807324379&sectionId=8938&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00016_196653_1517807324379
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act and the Statutes--`
  line
  line `(a) the first Chancellor, members of the Court, the Executive Council and the Academic Council`
  line `shall be nominated by the Visitor and shall hold office for a term of three years;`
  line
  line `(b) the first Vice-Chancellor shall be appointed by the Visitor and he shall hold office for a term`
  line `of five years.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (8939)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Amendment of Act 8 of 1922.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00016_196653_1517807324379&sectionId=8939&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00016_196653_1517807324379
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `In the Delhi University Act, 1922, in sub-section (2) of section`
  line `5, after the words "for the time being in force, the words and figures "but subject to the provisions`
  line `contained in the Jawaharlal Nehru University Act, 1966 shall be inserted.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
